==English==
===Etymology===

French ''[[#French|abatis]]'', ''[[abattis#French|abattis]]'', mass of things beaten or cut down, from ''[[abattre]]''. See ''[[abate]]''.

===Alternative spellings===
*[[abattis]]

===Noun===

{{en-noun|'''abatis '''or''' [[abatises]]'''}}

#A means of defense formed by felled trees, the ends of whose branches are [[sharpened]] and directed outwards, or against the enemy.

